<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1704208 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="979" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1.jpg 941w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1-782x598.jpg 782w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1-314x240.jpg 314w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1-627x480.jpg 627w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Rema-1-600x459.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Still basking in the release of his debut album Rave and Roses, Rema has hinted the release of the album’s deluxe version and a collaboration with Fireboy.   Connecting with fans following his return to Nigeria. Taking to Instagram, Rema shared a video of himself rehearsing Dirty, one of the album’s most popular songs, later asking fans to send in their questions in a post on his Instagram story. A fan asked, “Are we expecting a deluxe version?” to which Rema replied, “Yes.” <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1723080 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="2277" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2.jpeg 719w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2-336x598.jpeg 336w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2-648x1152.jpeg 648w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2-135x240.jpeg 135w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2-270x480.jpeg 270w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-a554b96fa2-337x600.jpeg 337w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> He further confirmed that he has multiple collaborations with Fireboy dml. “Do you have a song with Fireboy?” <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1723075 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="2274" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a.jpeg 720w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a-337x598.jpeg 337w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a-649x1152.jpeg 649w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a-135x240.jpeg 135w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a-270x480.jpeg 270w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ezgif-5-4148919c4a-338x600.jpeg 338w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Rema replied, “yes, more than one.” Woman crooner and afrobeat superstar Rema released his much-anticipated debut album, Rave & Roses, in March. Announcing the album’s release on Twitter, he wrote, “Here’s a piece of my soul to you, my debut Album Rave & roses out now. Thank you for the love & support over the years now; RAVE relentlessly! #RaveAndRoses. “ Speaking to Apple Music about the album, he said, “I swear this album has different moods, different stories.” He also noted that every project holds different meanings to him asides from the story they tell and said, “it’s that bridge to bring the fans closer to Rema.”  